Vimetco NV (VICO)  selected three companies
for a shortlist of contractors to build a planned 250 megawatt
gas-fired power plant in the southeastern Romanian city of
Tulcea, the company said in a statement on its website today.  The Amsterdam-based aluminum maker picked a group made up
of  Itochu Corp. (8001)  and Hyundai Engineering & Construction Co.,
Greeceâ€™s  Metka SA (METTK)  and  Siemens AG (SIE)  for further talks on the power
plant construction contract after receiving bids from seven
companies. The negotiations should be completed by the end of
May, Vimetco said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
